 from rice paddies (1984) J Atoms Chem, 1, pp. 241-268; Shannon, R.D., White, J.R., A 3-year study of controls on methane emission and from two Michigan peat lands (1994) Biogeochemistry, 27, pp. 35-60; Van Cleemput, O., Ramon, H., Vermoessen, A., Emission of C1-C3 hydrocarbons from soils (1991) Proc. of EUROTRAC Symposium 1990, pp. 189-191. , The Hague, Netherlands; Van der Nat, F.J.W.A., Middburg, J.J., Van Materen, D., Wielemakers, A., Diel methane emission patterns from Scirpus lacustris and Phragmites australis (1998) Biogeochemistry, 41, pp. 1-22; Verma, A., Subramanian, V., Ramesh, R., Day-time variation in methane emission from two tropical wetlands in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India (1999) Curr Sci, 76 (7), pp. 1020-1022; Wang, M., Shangguan, X.J., CH4 emission from various rice fields in P.R. China (1996) Theor Appl Climatol, 55, pp. 129-138; Wang, Z., DeLaune, R.D., Patrick, W.H., Methane production from anaerobic soil amended with rice straw and nitrogen fertilizers (1992) Fertil Res, 33, pp. 115-121; Wang, Z., DeLaune, R.D., Masscheleyn, P.H., Patrick, W.H., Soil redox and pH effects on methane production in a flooded rice soil (1993) Soil Sci Soc Am J, 57, pp. 382-385; Wang, Z., Lindau, C.W., DeLaune, R.D., Patrick, W.H., Methane emission and entrapment in flooded rice soils as affected by soil properties (1993) Biol Fertil Soils, 16, pp. 163-168; Wassmann, R., Neue, H.-U., Lantin, R.S., Aduna, J.B., Alberto, M.C.R., Flores, M.J.F., Tan, M.J.P., Sellier, W., Temporal patterns of methane emissions from wetland rice field treated by different modes of N-application (1994) J Geophys Res, 99, pp. 16457-16462; Yagi, K., Minami, K., Emission and production of methane in the paddy fields of Japan (1991) JARQ, 25, pp. 165-171","Singh, S.N.; Environmental Science Division, National Botanical Research Inst., Rana Pratap Marg, Lucknow 226001, India",,,,,,,,01604120,,ENVID,11686637,"English","Environ. Int.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0034771860
